  "texts": [
    "In this section, we look at available concept and training datasets that are relevant to the concept-supported research domain, as summarised in Tables 7 and 8.",
    "CUB-Caltech-UCSD birds-200-2011 The CUB dataset [102] contains 11,788 samples from 200 different bird species (e.g., Acadian Flycatcher, American Crow, Cardinal), as shown in Fig. 9.",
    "Each sample was annotated with bird categories, 15 part location classes, 28 attribute-groupings, 312 concept attributes in binary format (Exists, Doesn't Exist), certainty level (Not Visible, Guessing, Probably, Definitely), and a single bird bounding box.",
    "In concept-supported modelling, CUB is the most useful probe dataset.",
    "To achieve more accurate results, some studies, such as [87-89, 93, 98, 160, 164] used 112 concept labels that appear for equal or greater than ten classes."
